  • java.lang.Object

  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    TreeNodeDynamicSize, TreeNodeFixedSize
    abstract class TreeNode<KEY,​VALUE>
extends Object
    Methods to manipulate single tree node such as set and get header fields, insert and fetch keys, values and children.

      • insertSlotsAt

        static void insertSlotsAt​(PageCursor cursor,
                          int pos,
                          int numberOfSlots,
                          int totalSlotCount,
                          int baseOffset,
                          int slotSize)
        Moves data from left to right to open up a gap where data can later be written without overwriting anything. Key count is NOT updated!
        Parameters:
        cursor - Write cursor on relevant page
        pos - Logical position where slots should be inserted, pos is based on baseOffset and slotSize.
        numberOfSlots - How many slots to be inserted.
        totalSlotCount - How many slots there are in total. (Usually keyCount for keys and values or keyCount+1 for children).
        baseOffset - Offset to slot in logical position 0.
        slotSize - Size of one single slot.

      • removeSlotAt

        static void removeSlotAt​(PageCursor cursor,
                         int pos,
                         int totalSlotCount,
                         int baseOffset,
                         int slotSize)
        Moves data from right to left to remove a slot where data that should be deleted currently sits. Key count is NOT updated!
        Parameters:
        cursor - Write cursor on relevant page
        pos - Logical position where slots should be inserted, pos is based on baseOffset and slotSize.
        totalSlotCount - How many slots there are in total. (Usually keyCount for keys and values or keyCount+1 for children).
        baseOffset - Offset to slot in logical position 0.
        slotSize - Size of one single slot.

      • canRebalanceLeaves

        abstract int canRebalanceLeaves​(PageCursor leftCursor,
                                int leftKeyCount,
                                PageCursor rightCursor,
                                int rightKeyCount)
        How do we best rebalance left and right leaf? Can we move keys from underflowing left to right so that none of them underflow?
        Returns:
        0, do nothing. -1, merge. 1-inf, move this number of keys from left to right.

      • doSplitLeaf

        abstract void doSplitLeaf​(PageCursor leftCursor,
                          int leftKeyCount,
                          PageCursor rightCursor,
                          int insertPos,
                          KEY newKey,
                          VALUE newValue,
                          KEY newSplitter,
                          double ratioToKeepInLeftOnSplit,
                          long stableGeneration,
                          long unstableGeneration,
                          PageCursorTracer cursorTracer)
                   throws IOException
        Calculate where split should be done and move entries between leaves participating in split. Keys and values from left are divide between left and right and the new key and value is inserted where it belongs. Key count is updated.
        Throws:
        IOException

                       throws IOException
        Performs the entry moving part of split in internal. Keys and children from left is divided between left and right and the new key and child is inserted where it belongs. Key count is updated.
